<!-- ==================== 1. INTRODUCTION ==================== -->
<h2>1. Introduction &amp; System Overview</h2>
<p>The <strong>Campus Event &amp; Society Management System (CESMS)</strong> is a full-stack web application designed to streamline the management of student societies and their events at FAST-NUCES Karachi. It replaces scattered manual processes with a centralized platform providing role-based access for administrators, society heads, and students.</p>

<h3>Problem Statement</h3>
<p>In many universities, event management is handled manually or through scattered platforms, leading to poor communication, inefficient registration processes, lack of attendance tracking, and difficulty in gathering feedback. CESMS solves these problems by providing a single unified platform.</p>

<h3>Key Capabilities</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Event Management</strong> &mdash; Society heads create events; admins approve before publication</li>
  <li><strong>Student Registration</strong> &mdash; Students register/unregister with server-side capacity enforcement</li>
  <li><strong>Attendance Tracking</strong> &mdash; Society heads mark attendance per participant per event</li>
  <li><strong>Feedback System</strong> &mdash; Students rate (1&ndash;5 stars) and comment after attending events</li>
  <li><strong>Event Change Requests</strong> &mdash; Society heads request updates/deletes; admins approve/reject with reasons</li>
  <li><strong>Notifications</strong> &mdash; Society heads receive notifications when their requests are resolved</li>
  <li><strong>Venue Management</strong> &mdash; Admins manage venue availability; unavailable venues cannot be assigned to events</li>
  <li><strong>Role-Based Access</strong> &mdash; Three roles: Admin, Society Head, Student &mdash; each with their own dashboard</li>
  <li><strong>SQL Console</strong> &mdash; Built-in admin SQL console with database inspector for direct queries</li>
  <li><strong>Search &amp; Filtering</strong> &mdash; Client-side search on the public events page</li>
</ul>

<hr class="divider"/>

<!-- ==================== 2. TECH STACK ==================== -->
<h2>2. Technology Stack</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th style="width:25%;">Layer</th><th>Technology</th><th style="width:30%;">Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Frontend Framework</strong></td><td>React 19 + TypeScript</td><td>Single-page application with Vite 6</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Styling</strong></td><td>Tailwind CSS 4</td><td>Utility-first CSS with glass-morphism design</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Animations</strong></td><td>Framer Motion</td><td>Page transitions, hover effects, staggered lists</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Icons</strong></td><td>Lucide React</td><td>Consistent icon set across all dashboards</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Routing</strong></td><td>React Router v7</td><td>Client-side routing with protected routes</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Backend</strong></td><td>Node.js + Express 4</td><td>RESTful API with TypeScript (tsx runtime)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Database (Production)</strong></td><td>PostgreSQL</td><td>Hosted via Neon/Render with SSL</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Database (Local Dev)</strong></td><td>SQLite (better-sqlite3)</td><td>Zero-config local development</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Authentication</strong></td><td>Cookie-based sessions</td><td>HTTP-only cookies with 30-day expiry</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Deployment</strong></td><td>Render</td><td>Single-service deployment (Express serves React)</td></tr>
</table>

<hr class="divider"/>

<!-- ==================== 3. ARCHITECTURE ==================== -->
<h2>3. System Architecture</h2>
<p>The application follows a <strong>monolithic full-stack architecture</strong> where a single Express server serves both the React frontend and the REST API.</p>

<h3>Request Flow</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Step</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td>Browser sends request to Express server</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td>API routes (<code>/api/*</code>) are handled by Express with database queries</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>Protected routes use <code>authMiddleware</code> to verify cookie-based session</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td>Role checks (<code>ADMIN</code>, <code>SOCIETY_HEAD</code>, <code>STUDENT</code>) enforce permissions</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td>All other routes serve the React SPA (Vite dev middleware or static dist/)</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Database Abstraction</h3>
<p>The server uses a unified database wrapper supporting both PostgreSQL and SQLite. A <code>toPgSql()</code> helper converts SQLite <code>?</code> placeholders to PostgreSQL <code>$1, $2...</code> style. PostgreSQL bigint values are parsed as JavaScript numbers to prevent string concatenation bugs.</p>

<hr class="divider"/>

<!-- ==================== 4. DATABASE DESIGN ==================== -->
<h2>4. Database Design</h2>
<p>The database consists of <strong>11 tables</strong> with <strong>14 foreign key relationships</strong>, <strong>12 CHECK constraints</strong>, and <strong>8 UNIQUE constraints</strong>.</p>

<h3>4.1 Entity-Relationship Overview</h3>
<pre style="background:#f4f6f9; padding:15px; border-radius:5px; font-size:10pt; line-height:1.5; overflow-x:auto;">
users (id) &lt;─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │                                                                           │
  ├── societies.head_id          (ON DELETE SET NULL)                         │
  ├── societies.co_head_id      (ON DELETE SET NULL)                         │
  ├── societies.admin_id         (ON DELETE SET NULL)                         │
  │                                                                            │
venues (id)                                                                  │
  └── events.venue_id           (ON DELETE RESTRICT)                         │
                                                                             │
societies (id)                                                               │
  ├── events.society_id         (ON DELETE CASCADE)                          │
  ├── heads.society_id          (ON DELETE SET NULL)                         │
  ├── co_heads.society_id       (ON DELETE SET NULL)                         │
  └── student_members.society_id (ON DELETE SET NULL)                        │
                                                                             │
events (id)                                                                  │
  ├── registrations.event_id    (ON DELETE CASCADE)                          │
  ├── feedback.event_id         (ON DELETE CASCADE)                          │
  └── event_requests.event_id   (ON DELETE CASCADE)                         │
                                                                             │
users (id) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
  ├── registrations.user_id     (ON DELETE CASCADE)
  ├── feedback.user_id          (ON DELETE CASCADE)
  └── event_requests.head_id    (ON DELETE CASCADE)
</pre>

<h3>4.2 Complete Table Definitions</h3>

<!-- USERS -->
<h4>Table: <code>users</code> &mdash; Unified authentication table for all roles</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>email</td><td>TEXT</td><td>UNIQUE NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>password</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>role</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL DEFAULT 'STUDENT', CHECK(role IN ('ADMIN','SOCIETY_HEAD','STUDENT'))</td></tr>
  <tr><td>roll_no</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>phone</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- VENUES -->
<h4>Table: <code>venues</code> &mdash; Campus event locations</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>location</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>capacity</td><td>INTEGER</td><td>NOT NULL, CHECK(capacity > 0)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>availability</td><td>TEXT</td><td>DEFAULT 'YES', CHECK(availability IN ('YES','NO'))</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- SOCIETIES -->
<h4>Table: <code>societies</code> &mdash; Student organizations</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL UNIQUE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>description</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>category</td><td>TEXT</td><td>CHECK(category IN ('TECHNICAL','CULTURAL','LITERARY','SPORTS','SOCIAL') OR NULL)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>established_year</td><td>INTEGER</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>contact_email</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>vision</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>head_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>co_head_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>status</td><td>TEXT</td><td>DEFAULT 'APPROVED', CHECK(status IN ('APPROVED','PENDING','REJECTED'))</td></tr>
  <tr><td>admin_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- EVENTS -->
<h4>Table: <code>events</code> &mdash; Society events</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>title</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>description</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>date</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>time</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>capacity</td><td>INTEGER</td><td>NOT NULL, CHECK(capacity > 0)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>society_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, REFERENCES societies(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>venue_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, REFERENCES venues(id) ON DELETE RESTRICT</td></tr>
  <tr><td>head_email</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>status</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL DEFAULT 'PENDING', CHECK(status IN ('PENDING','PUBLISHED','CANCELLED'))</td></tr>
  <tr><td>created_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- REGISTRATIONS -->
<h4>Table: <code>registrations</code> &mdash; Student event registrations</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>user_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>event_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, REFERENCES events(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>status</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL DEFAULT 'REGISTERED', CHECK(status IN ('REGISTERED','ATTENDED','CANCELLED'))</td></tr>
  <tr><td>registered_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3"><strong>UNIQUE(user_id, event_id)</strong> &mdash; prevents duplicate registrations</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ADMINS -->
<h4>Table: <code>admins</code> &mdash; Admin registry</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>email</td><td>TEXT</td><td>UNIQUE NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>password</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>department</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>access_level</td><td>TEXT</td><td>DEFAULT 'FULL', CHECK(access_level IN ('FULL','LIMITED'))</td></tr>
  <tr><td>phone</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>created_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- HEADS -->
<h4>Table: <code>heads</code> &mdash; Society head registry</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>email</td><td>TEXT</td><td>UNIQUE NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>password</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>society_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>REFERENCES societies(id) ON DELETE SET NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>department</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>phone</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>tenure_start</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>created_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- CO_HEADS -->
<h4>Table: <code>co_heads</code> &mdash; Society co-head registry</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>email</td><td>TEXT</td><td>UNIQUE NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>password</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>society_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>REFERENCES societies(id) ON DELETE SET NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>department</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>phone</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>tenure_start</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>created_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- STUDENT_MEMBERS -->
<h4>Table: <code>student_members</code> &mdash; Student member registry</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>email</td><td>TEXT</td><td>UNIQUE NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>password</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>society_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>REFERENCES societies(id) ON DELETE SET NULL</td></tr>
  <tr><td>roll_no</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>department</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>semester</td><td>INTEGER</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>phone</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>joined_date</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>created_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- FEEDBACK -->
<h4>Table: <code>feedback</code> &mdash; Event ratings and comments</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>user_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>event_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, REFERENCES events(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>rating</td><td>INTEGER</td><td>NOT NULL, CHECK(rating >= 1 AND rating <= 5)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>comments</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>created_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td></tr>
  <tr><td colspan="3"><strong>UNIQUE(user_id, event_id)</strong> &mdash; one feedback per user per event</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- EVENT_REQUESTS -->
<h4>Table: <code>event_requests</code> &mdash; Society head change requests</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>PRIMARY KEY</td></tr>
  <tr><td>event_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, REFERENCES events(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>head_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>request_type</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL, CHECK(request_type IN ('UPDATE','DELETE'))</td></tr>
  <tr><td>status</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL DEFAULT 'PENDING', CHECK(status IN ('PENDING','APPROVED','REJECTED'))</td></tr>
  <tr><td>reason</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>admin_reason</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>proposed_title</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>proposed_description</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>proposed_date</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>proposed_time</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>proposed_capacity</td><td>INTEGER</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>proposed_venue_id</td><td>TEXT</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
  <tr><td>created_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td></tr>
  <tr><td>resolved_at</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>4.3 Foreign Key Relationships (14 total)</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Table</th><th>Column</th><th>References</th><th>ON DELETE</th><th>Why</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td>societies</td><td>head_id</td><td>users(id)</td><td>SET NULL</td><td>If user deleted, society keeps its data but loses head assignment</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td>societies</td><td>co_head_id</td><td>users(id)</td><td>SET NULL</td><td>Same as above for co-head</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>societies</td><td>admin_id</td><td>users(id)</td><td>SET NULL</td><td>Society loses admin link but survives</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td>events</td><td>society_id</td><td>societies(id)</td><td>CASCADE</td><td>Delete society &rarr; delete all its events</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td>events</td><td>venue_id</td><td>venues(id)</td><td>RESTRICT</td><td>Cannot delete venue with assigned events</td></tr>
  <tr><td>6</td><td>registrations</td><td>user_id</td><td>users(id)</td><td>CASCADE</td><td>Delete user &rarr; delete their registrations</td></tr>
  <tr><td>7</td><td>registrations</td><td>event_id</td><td>events(id)</td><td>CASCADE</td><td>Delete event &rarr; delete its registrations</td></tr>
  <tr><td>8</td><td>feedback</td><td>user_id</td><td>users(id)</td><td>CASCADE</td><td>Delete user &rarr; delete their feedback</td></tr>
  <tr><td>9</td><td>feedback</td><td>event_id</td><td>events(id)</td><td>CASCADE</td><td>Delete event &rarr; delete its feedback</td></tr>
  <tr><td>10</td><td>event_requests</td><td>event_id</td><td>events(id)</td><td>CASCADE</td><td>Delete event &rarr; delete related requests</td></tr>
  <tr><td>11</td><td>event_requests</td><td>head_id</td><td>users(id)</td><td>CASCADE</td><td>Delete user &rarr; delete their requests</td></tr>
  <tr><td>12</td><td>heads</td><td>society_id</td><td>societies(id)</td><td>SET NULL</td><td>Delete society &rarr; head record stays (unlinked)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>13</td><td>co_heads</td><td>society_id</td><td>societies(id)</td><td>SET NULL</td><td>Same as above</td></tr>
  <tr><td>14</td><td>student_members</td><td>society_id</td><td>societies(id)</td><td>SET NULL</td><td>Same as above</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>4.4 CHECK Constraints (12 total)</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Table</th><th>Constraint</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td>users</td><td>role IN ('ADMIN','SOCIETY_HEAD','STUDENT')</td><td>Only valid roles allowed</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td>venues</td><td>capacity > 0</td><td>Venue must hold at least 1 person</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>venues</td><td>availability IN ('YES','NO')</td><td>Only valid availability values</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td>societies</td><td>status IN ('APPROVED','PENDING','REJECTED')</td><td>Only valid approval statuses</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td>societies</td><td>category IN ('TECHNICAL','CULTURAL','LITERARY','SPORTS','SOCIAL') or NULL</td><td>Only valid categories</td></tr>
  <tr><td>6</td><td>events</td><td>status IN ('PENDING','PUBLISHED','CANCELLED')</td><td>Only valid event statuses</td></tr>
  <tr><td>7</td><td>events</td><td>capacity > 0</td><td>Event must hold at least 1 person</td></tr>
  <tr><td>8</td><td>registrations</td><td>status IN ('REGISTERED','ATTENDED','CANCELLED')</td><td>Only valid registration states</td></tr>
  <tr><td>9</td><td>admins</td><td>access_level IN ('FULL','LIMITED')</td><td>Only valid access levels</td></tr>
  <tr><td>10</td><td>feedback</td><td>rating >= 1 AND rating <= 5</td><td>Star rating must be 1&ndash;5</td></tr>
  <tr><td>11</td><td>event_requests</td><td>request_type IN ('UPDATE','DELETE')</td><td>Only valid request types</td></tr>
  <tr><td>12</td><td>event_requests</td><td>status IN ('PENDING','APPROVED','REJECTED')</td><td>Only valid request statuses</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>4.5 UNIQUE Constraints</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Table</th><th>Column(s)</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td>users</td><td>email</td><td>No two users share an email</td></tr>
  <tr><td>societies</td><td>name</td><td>No two societies share a name</td></tr>
  <tr><td>admins</td><td>email</td><td>Unique admin emails</td></tr>
  <tr><td>heads</td><td>email</td><td>Unique head emails</td></tr>
  <tr><td>co_heads</td><td>email</td><td>Unique co-head emails</td></tr>
  <tr><td>student_members</td><td>email</td><td>Unique member emails</td></tr>
  <tr><td>registrations</td><td>(user_id, event_id)</td><td>Prevents duplicate registrations</td></tr>
  <tr><td>feedback</td><td>(user_id, event_id)</td><td>One feedback per user per event</td></tr>
</table>

<hr class="divider"/>

<!-- ==================== 5. WORK DISTRIBUTION ==================== -->
<h2>5. Work Distribution</h2>
<p style="font-size:10pt; color:#666;">Work divided equally. Each member owns their modules end-to-end (backend + frontend).</p>

<table>
  <tr><th style="width:50%; background:#0f3460;">Mohammad Taha Anwar (24K-3033) &mdash; Group Lead</th><th style="width:50%; background:#155724;">Hamza Atif (24K-0594) &mdash; Co-Developer</th></tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <h4>Module 1: Project Architecture &amp; Setup</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Initialized project with Vite + React + TypeScript</li>
        <li>Configured dual-database support (PostgreSQL + SQLite)</li>
        <li>Set up Express server with Vite middleware integration</li>
        <li>Database abstraction layer with placeholder conversion</li>
        <li>PostgreSQL bigint type parser to prevent string bugs</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 2: Database Schema Design</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Designed all 11 tables with proper column types</li>
        <li>Defined 14 foreign key relationships with ON DELETE rules</li>
        <li>Added 12 CHECK constraints for data integrity</li>
        <li>Added 8 UNIQUE constraints to prevent duplicates</li>
        <li>Wrote migration system for existing databases (ALTER TABLE)</li>
        <li>Created seed data with 24 users, 7 venues, 6 societies, 10 events, 32 registrations</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 3: Authentication &amp; Security</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Cookie-based session with HTTP-only flag and 30-day expiry</li>
        <li>Auth middleware for protected routes</li>
        <li>Role-based access control (RBAC) on all endpoints</li>
        <li>AuthContext provider for React session persistence</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 4: Admin Module (Full Stack)</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>15+ admin API endpoints (CRUD for all entities)</li>
        <li>Event approval/rejection workflow</li>
        <li>Event change request review (approve/reject with reasons)</li>
        <li>Society management (create, delete, assign head/co-head)</li>
        <li>Venue management (toggle availability, add, delete)</li>
        <li>User management tables (admins, heads, co-heads, members)</li>
        <li>SQL Console with live query execution</li>
        <li>Full database inspector (browse every table)</li>
        <li>Admin Dashboard GUI with stats, tables, modals</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 5: Event Request/Approval Workflow</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>event_requests table with proposed_* columns</li>
        <li>Society head submits UPDATE/DELETE requests</li>
        <li>Admin approves (applies changes) or rejects (with reason)</li>
        <li>Notification system for society heads</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 6: Venue Management</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>availability field with YES/NO constraint</li>
        <li>Server-side validation: unavailable venues rejected on event creation</li>
        <li>Server-side validation: event capacity cannot exceed venue capacity</li>
        <li>Cannot delete venue with assigned events (RESTRICT FK)</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 7: Deployment</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Render deployment with PostgreSQL database</li>
        <li>Environment-based configuration (dev vs production)</li>
        <li>Production: Express serves built React static files</li>
      </ul>
    </td>
    <td>
      <h4>Module 1: Frontend Architecture &amp; UI Design</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Designed glass-morphism theme with Tailwind CSS</li>
        <li>Responsive layout system for all screen sizes</li>
        <li>Framer Motion animation system (page transitions, stagger, hover)</li>
        <li>Consistent component design language across all dashboards</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 2: Landing Page &amp; Public Event Browsing</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Hero section with FAST CLUSTERS branding</li>
        <li>Live countdown timer on every event card</li>
        <li>Client-side search filtering (by title and society name)</li>
        <li>Feature highlights section</li>
        <li>Footer with developer credits</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 3: Login System</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Email/password login form with error handling</li>
        <li>Quick-login demo buttons for 5 pre-configured accounts</li>
        <li>Session persistence with AuthContext</li>
        <li>Automatic redirect to role-specific dashboard</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 4: Student Module (Full Stack)</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Student registration API with capacity enforcement</li>
        <li>Student unregistration API (sets status to CANCELLED)</li>
        <li>Re-registration support (CANCELLED &rarr; REGISTERED)</li>
        <li>Student Dashboard: available events, registered events, attended events</li>
        <li>Star-rating feedback modal (1&ndash;5 stars + comments)</li>
        <li>Unregister button on registered events</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 5: Society Head Module (Full Stack)</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Event creation API with venue availability check</li>
        <li>Attendance tracking API (mark REGISTERED &rarr; ATTENDED)</li>
        <li>Feedback viewing API for society head's events</li>
        <li>Event request submission API (UPDATE/DELETE)</li>
        <li>Society Head Dashboard: stats, events table, actions</li>
        <li>Participants modal with attendance toggle per student</li>
        <li>Feedback viewer modal per event</li>
        <li>Edit request modal (pre-filled event data)</li>
        <li>Delete request modal (with reason input)</li>
        <li>Notification panel for resolved requests</li>
        <li>Recent feedback overview section</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 6: Shared Components</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>EventCard component with countdown timer, capacity bar, register/full states</li>
        <li>Navigation bar with mobile drawer</li>
        <li>AuthContext provider (login, logout, refresh, ProtectedRoute)</li>
        <li>PrivateRoute wrapper for protected dashboard</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Module 7: Testing &amp; Quality Assurance</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Cross-browser testing (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)</li>
        <li>Mobile responsiveness testing</li>
        <li>Role-based access verification</li>
        <li>Data integrity validation across all workflows</li>
      </ul>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

