<!-- ==================== 8. USER ROLES ==================== -->
<h2>8. User Roles &amp; Permissions</h2>

<h3>Administrator</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Capability</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Approve/reject events</td><td>Reviews society head event submissions before publication</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Approve/reject event change requests</td><td>Reviews UPDATE/DELETE requests with reasons for rejection</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Manage societies</td><td>Create, delete, assign head/co-head</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Manage venues</td><td>Add, delete, toggle availability</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Manage users</td><td>View all users; CRUD for admins, heads, co-heads, student members</td></tr>
  <tr><td>SQL Console</td><td>Execute arbitrary SQL queries and browse entire database</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Society Head</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Capability</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Create events</td><td>Submit events for admin approval (only available venues shown)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>View participants</td><td>See registered students for each event</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Mark attendance</td><td>Toggle attendance status per participant</td></tr>
  <tr><td>View feedback</td><td>See ratings and comments for all own events</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Request event edits</td><td>Submit update requests (admin must approve)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Request event deletion</td><td>Submit delete requests with reason (admin must approve)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>View notifications</td><td>See approved/rejected request resolutions</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Student</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Capability</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Browse events</td><td>View all published events on landing page and dashboard</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Register for events</td><td>One-click registration (capacity enforced server-side)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Unregister</td><td>Cancel registration for upcoming events</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Submit feedback</td><td>Rate (1&ndash;5 stars) and comment on attended events</td></tr>
  <tr><td>View registered events</td><td>See all current and past registrations</td></tr>
</table>

